   - find more bugs

@endnode

@node "xanim"
@title "XAnim"

 The QuickTime encodings supported by CyberQT are based on the  source  code  to
 Mark Podlipec's XAnim program. XAnim supports a number of other QuickTime video
 encodings, as well as AVI files.

   The key differences between CyberQT and XAnim for QuickTime files are:

     - XAnim is more powerful and more general than CyberQT.

     - CyberQT requires either a CyberGraphX compatible graphic board or AGA
       chipset. ECS is not and will not be supported!



    A gzip compressed archive of Mark Podlipec's XAnim can be obtained from:

       http://www.portal.com/~podlipec/home.html  "The XAnim Home Page"


